<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Our Voyage to Learning — A Story</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&family=Lato:wght@300;400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    background: #f4f1ec;
    font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0 0 3rem;
  }

  .banner {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 220px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 30%;
    display: block;
  }

  .book-wrapper {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .book-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #6b6b6b;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .book-scene {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 620px;
  }

  .book {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
  }

  .page {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: 4px 12px 12px 4px;
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 0.5px solid #ccc;
    padding: 2.5rem 2.8rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: rotateY(-8deg);
    transition: opacity 0.45s ease, transform 0.45s ease;
    pointer-events: none;
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 -1px #e0ddd8, 8px 8px 0 -2px #d6d3ce;
  }

  .page.active {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: rotateY(0deg);
    pointer-events: all;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .page-spine {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 8px;
    height: 100%;
    background: #f0ece5;
    border-radius: 4px 0 0 4px;
    border-right: 0.5px solid #d5d0c8;
  }

  .page-num {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: #aaa;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-align: right;
  }

  .chapter-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #aaa;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .page-heading {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 21px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
  }

  .page-heading em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .page-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #444;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .page-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid #1D9E75;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 14.5px;
    color: #222;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .page-footer {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding-top: 0.9rem;
    border-top: 0.5px solid #e0ddd8;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }

  .anchor-icon {
    font-size: 15px;
    opacity: 0.3;
  }

  .cover-page .page-heading {
    font-size: 28px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .cover-page .subtitle {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #6b6b6b;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .cover-page .cover-body {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .cover-divider {
    width: 60px;
    height: 2px;
    background: #1D9E75;
    margin: 0.8rem auto 1rem;
  }

  .nav-area {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
  }

  .nav-btn {
    background: #fff;
    border: 0.5px solid #bbb;
    border-radius: 50%;
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition: background 0.15s, transform 0.1s;
    color: #333;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .nav-btn:hover { background: #f0ece5; }
  .nav-btn:active { transform: scale(0.95); }
  .nav-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.3; cursor: default; }
  .nav-btn:disabled:hover { background: #fff; }

  .progress-dots {
    display: flex;
    gap: 7px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .dot {
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #ccc;
    transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .dot.active {
    background: #1D9E75;
    transform: scale(1.45);
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .book { height: 460px; }
    .page { padding: 1.8rem 1.6rem; }
    .page-heading { font-size: 18px; }
    .page-body { font-size: 13px; }
    .cover-page .page-heading { font-size: 22px; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<img class="banner" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Voyage to Learning 4.5 banner — OCSS"/>

<div class="book-wrapper">
  <div class="book-title">Oglethorpe County Schools &nbsp;•&nbsp; Voyage to Learning 4.5</div>

  <div class="book-scene">
    <div class="book" id="book">

      <div class="page cover-page active" data-page="0">
        <div class="page-spine"></div>
        <div>
          <div class="chapter-label">February 20, 2026</div>
          <div class="page-heading">Our <em>Voyage</em> to Learning</div>
          <div class="subtitle">A story told by the educators who lived it</div>
          <div class="cover-divider"></div>
          <div class="cover-body">
            On February 20, 2026, 280+ educators gathered, presented,<br>and learned together at VTL 4.5.<br><br>
            This is the story they wrote — in their own words.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="page-footer">
          <span class="anchor-icon">⚓</span>
          <div class="page-num">Cover</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page" data-page="1">
        <div class="page-spine"></div>
        <div>
          <div class="chapter-label">Chapter One</div>
          <div class="page-heading">A <em>Powerhouse</em> Team Sets Sail</div>
          <div class="page-body">
            The day began with unmistakable energy. Educators arrived knowing they were part of something meaningful — a gathering of innovators right here in Oglethorpe County, offering tools and strategies that rivaled any costly conference.
            <div class="page-quote">"Oglethorpe County — we are a powerhouse team of innovators and leaders."</div>
            As participants settled in, the buy-in was immediate. Participation was "genuine and honest," and many felt they were finally among like-minded people, free to explore and dream together.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="page-footer">
          <span class="anchor-icon">⚓</span>
          <div class="page-num">1 / 5</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page" data-page="2">
        <div class="page-spine"></div>
        <div>
          <div class="chapter-label">Chapter Two</div>
          <div class="page-heading">Collaboration <em>at Every Port</em></div>
          <div class="page-body">
            Throughout the day, something remarkable happened in classrooms and hallways alike: educators built off each other's ideas, presented alongside their closest colleagues, and connected with teachers from neighboring districts.
            <div class="page-quote">"As I looked across the classroom, I was filled with genuine pride for my co-collaborators and gratitude for the people I work with."</div>
            One educator even received a request to bring her session back to an entire department in another district — proof that the work here reaches far beyond county lines.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="page-footer">
          <span class="anchor-icon">⚓</span>
          <div class="page-num">2 / 5</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page" data-page="3">
        <div class="page-spine"></div>
        <div>
          <div class="chapter-label">Chapter Three</div>
          <div class="page-heading">A New <em>Horizon</em> for AI</div>
          <div class="page-body">
            The topic of artificial intelligence wove through nearly every session. Teachers left not with fear, but with curiosity — and ideas they couldn't stop exploring.
            <div class="page-quote">"My mind was running on ALL cylinders... I kept slipping further and further down MULTIPLE rabbit holes."</div>
            The consensus was clear: AI can "drastically improve instructional preparedness" and make teaching "more engaging than ever." Some found they could take an idea "full circle to fruition." The future would be "complex, but exciting."
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="page-footer">
          <span class="anchor-icon">⚓</span>
          <div class="page-num">3 / 5</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page" data-page="4">
        <div class="page-spine"></div>
        <div>
          <div class="chapter-label">Chapter Four</div>
          <div class="page-heading">Empathy, <em>Connection</em>, and Reflection</div>
          <div class="page-body">
            Not every moment was about technology. Some of the day's deepest impact came from sessions that opened eyes and softened hearts — a simulation of life as a SPED student, a sobering look at gang crime's reach into students' lives.
            <div class="page-quote">"It prompted me to reflect on my instructional practices and consider how I can better support their diverse needs."</div>
            These moments reminded every educator why they came: not just to learn tools, but to become better for the students who walk the halls each day.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="page-footer">
          <span class="anchor-icon">⚓</span>
          <div class="page-num">4 / 5</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page" data-page="5">
        <div class="page-spine"></div>
        <div>
          <div class="chapter-label">Epilogue</div>
          <div class="page-heading"><em>Lift All Tides</em></div>
          <div class="page-body">
            When educators left VTL 4.5, they carried something new — not just tools and strategies, but a renewed sense of purpose. One teacher put it simply, sharing the words she tells her students every day:
            <div class="page-quote">"You should never stop learning because life will never stop teaching."</div>
            Voyage to Learning didn't just offer professional development. It set out to lift all tides — and for one day, it absolutely did.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="page-footer">
          <span class="anchor-icon">⚓</span>
          <div class="page-num">5 / 5</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="nav-area">
    <button class="nav-btn" id="prev-btn" disabled>&#8592;</button>
    <div class="progress-dots" id="dots"></div>
    <button class="nav-btn" id="next-btn">&#8594;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  const totalPages = 6;
  let current = 0;
  const pages = document.querySelectorAll('.page');
  const dotsEl = document.getElementById('dots');
  const prevBtn = document.getElementById('prev-btn');
  const nextBtn = document.getElementById('next-btn');

  for (let i = 0; i < totalPages; i++) {
    const d = document.createElement('div');
    d.className = 'dot' + (i === 0 ? ' active' : '');
    d.addEventListener('click', () => goTo(i));
    dotsEl.appendChild(d);
  }

  function goTo(n) {
    pages[current].classList.remove('active');
    dotsEl.children[current].classList.remove('active');
    current = n;
    pages[current].classList.add('active');
    dotsEl.children[current].classList.add('active');
    prevBtn.disabled = current === 0;
    nextBtn.disabled = current === totalPages - 1;
  }

  prevBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (current > 0) goTo(current - 1); });
  nextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (current < totalPages - 1) goTo(current + 1); });
</script>

</body>
</html>
